level.heading: FAILURE TO FILE A BIENNIAL REPORT (§ 17-706)

level.text: 706.1 If a domestic entity required to file a biennial report under § 702ails to file a timely biennial report, the failure to timely file shall berounds for administrative dissolution of the domestic entity by theuperintendent.

706.2 If a foreign entity required to file a biennial report under § 702ails to file a timely biennial report, the failure to timely file shall berounds for the termination of the foreign entity’s registration by theuperintendent.
